    <note type="biography">
        <p>Botanist and literary editor. Daughter of Leonard Horner. Married Henry Lyell, brother of Charles Lyell, in 1848. Compiled a geographical handbook of fern distribution in 1870. Her collection of plants from India was given to the British Museum; her fern collection was given to the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew. Edited <hi rend="italic">Life, letters and journals of Sir Charles Lyell</hi> (1881), and <hi rend="italic">Life and letters of Sir Charles J. F. Bunbury</hi> (1906).</p></note>
